hint: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this POKéMON.
name: bulbasaur

hint: When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.
name: ivysaur

hint: The plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.
name: venusaur

hint: Obviously prefers hot places. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.
name: charmander

hint: When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the temperature to unbearably high levels.
name: charmeleon

hint: Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to cause forest fires unintentionally.
name: charizard

hint: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. Powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.
name: squirtle

hint: Often hides in water to stalk unwary prey. For swimming fast, it moves its ears to maintain balance.
name: wartortle

hint: A brutal POKéMON with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high speed tackles.
name: blastoise

hint: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.
name: caterpie

hint: This POKéMON is vulnerable to attack while its shell is soft, exposing its weak and tender body.
name: metapod

hint: In battle, it flaps its wings at high speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.
name: butterfree

hint: Often found in forests, eating leaves. It has a sharp venomous stinger on its head.
name: weedle

hint: Almost incapable of moving, this POKéMON can only harden its shell to protect itself from predators.
name: kakuna

hint: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.
name: beedrill

hint: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.
name: pidgey

hint: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this POKéMON will fiercely peck at any intruder.
name: pidgeotto

hint: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as MAGIKARP.
name: pidgeot

hint: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.
name: rattata

hint: It uses its whis­ kers to maintain its balance. It apparently slows down if they are cut off.
name: raticate

hint: It flaps its small wings busily to fly. Using its beak, it searches in grass for prey.
name: spearow

hint: With its huge and magnificent wings, it can keep aloft without ever having to land for rest.
name: fearow

hint: Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole.
name: ekans

hint: It is rumored that the ferocious warning markings on its belly differ from area to area.
name: arbok

hint: When several of these POKéMON gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.
name: pikachu

hint: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high-voltage power.
name: raichu

hint: Burrows deep underground in arid locations far from water. It only emerges to hunt for food.
name: sandshrew

hint: Curls up into a spiny ball when threatened. It can roll while curled up to attack or escape.
name: sandslash

hint: Although small, its venomous barbs render this POKéMON dangerous. The female has smaller horns.
name: nidoran-f

hint: The female's horn develops slowly. Prefers physical attacks such as clawing and biting.
name: nidorina

hint: Its hard scales provide strong protection. It uses its hefty bulk to execute powerful moves.
name: nidoqueen

hint: Stiffens its ears to sense danger. The larger its horns, the more powerful its secreted venom.
name: nidoran-m

hint: An aggressive POKéMON that is quick to attack. The horn on its head secretes a powerful venom.
name: nidorino

hint: It uses its powerful tail in battle to smash, constrict, then break the prey's bones.
name: nidoking

hint: Its magical and cute appeal has many admirers. It is rare and found only in certain areas.
name: clefairy

hint: A timid fairy POKéMON that is rarely seen. It will run and hide the moment it senses people.
name: clefable

hint: At the time of birth, it has just one tail. The tail splits from its tip as it grows older.
name: vulpix

hint: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1000-year curse.
name: ninetales

hint: When its huge eyes light up, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.
name: jigglypuff

hint: The body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck in air and inflate itself to an enormous size.
name: wigglytuff

hint: Forms colonies in perpetually dark places. Uses ultrasonic waves to identify and approach targets.
name: zubat

hint: Once it strikes, it will not stop draining energy from the victim even if it gets too heavy to fly.
name: golbat

hint: During the day, it keeps its face buried in the ground. At night, it wanders around sowing its seeds.
name: oddish

hint: The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn't drool. It is a nectar that is used to attract prey.
name: gloom

hint: It has the world’s largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.
name: vileplume

hint: Burrows to suck tree roots. The mushrooms on its back grow by draw­ ing nutrients from the bug host.
name: paras

hint: A host-parasite pair in which the parasite mushroom has taken over the host bug. Prefers damp places.
name: parasect

hint: Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats insects. It is attracted by light at night.
name: venonat

hint: The dustlike scales covering its wings are color-coded to indicate the kinds of poison it has.
name: venomoth

hint: Lives about one yard underground where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears above ground.
name: diglett

hint: A team of DIGLETT triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.
name: dugtrio
